-- Electronic Arts loss narrows
-- 
-- Tue Jul 29, 2008 4:14pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/07/29/businesspro-electronic-arts-results-dc-idUSWNAB328120080729

 

 LOS ANGELES  (Reuters) - Video game maker Electronic Arts 
Inc ERTS.O posted a narrower quarterly loss on Tuesday and 
said its highly anticipated game Spore would debut on September 
7. 

  Net loss was $95 million, or 30 cents a share, compared 
with a year-ago loss of $132 million, or 42 cents a share, it 
said.  Net revenue rose to $804 million from $395 million a year 
ago.  (Reporting by  Jennifer Martinez )